&lt;p&gt;Advanced Podiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB PURPOSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To manage a caseload of Podiatry patients with specialised foot care needs involving triaging, planning, overseeing, delegating and co-ordinating care whilst ensuring diverse needs are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To take a lead responsibility for the specialist clinical practice, both ward and clinic based, to ensure high quality interventions and treatments are delivered in a timely and effective manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assess, diagnose, develop and implement individualised care programmes for a caseload of patients within the specialism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the effective delivery and delegation of clinical and administrative tasks to facilitate effective caseload management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be a source of specialist advice, training and support to team members and other staff, mentoring to assess competence and development needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To liaise with the Allied Health Professional Lead to propose service improvements, policy or services changes pertaining to the specialism. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To act as a source of professional specialist podiatry advice for healthcare professionals, patients and carers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There may be a requirement for the post holder to work outside of the core hours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
